=begin
  918wands - liquidate treasure wands with Duplicate (918)

  For a Wizard standing in any shop that buys wands - a pawnshop, Cendadric's
  Collectibles, etc.  Pulls each wand from a container, casts Duplicate (918)
  on it, and - if the copy is made - sells both the original and the copy.
  Repeats until no more duplicatable wands remain.  A non-destructive APPRAISE
  is used up front to confirm a buyer is present before anything is duplicated.

  Default container:
    The container you've set as your WAND stow target in-game (STOW WAND
    <container>).  918wands reads Lich's StowList, the same source eloot uses
    to know which sack holds which item type, so "the wand sack" is found
    automatically.  Override with a container noun, or use "all".

  Why this is safe for "keeper" wands:
    Duplicate only works on items still "fresh" from the treasure system.  A
    wand that ISN'T a fresh treasure wand simply fails with "not well suited
    for duplicating" and is placed back in the container untouched and
    UNSOLD.  We only ever sell wands that successfully duplicated.

  Duplicate (918) mechanics (per wiki):
    - Item in the RIGHT hand, LEFT hand empty; copy lands in the left hand.
    - Each item can be duplicated only once (both become immune after).
    - Small chance of catastrophic failure -> the wand is destroyed.

  Mana recovery (Duplicate costs 18 mana):
    Optionally use your society's mana ability while waiting - Sign of Wracking
    (Council of Light), Symbol of Mana (Order of Voln), or Sigil of Power
    (Guardians of Sunfist).  Enable the one for your society; only the matching
    ability is ever used.  Modeled on ewaggle's mana handling.

  Never-sell exclusions:
    Add name phrases (like eloot's sell-exclude) so matching wands are never
    duplicated or sold - useful for keeper wands stored in the same container.

  Usage:
    ;918wands                  - process wands in your WAND stow container
    ;918wands all              - process wands in EVERY worn container
    ;918wands <container>      - process wands in <container> (noun)
    ;918wands wracking on|off  - Sign of Wracking recovery (Council of Light)
    ;918wands mana on|off      - Symbol of Mana recovery (Order of Voln)
    ;918wands power on|off     - Sigil of Power recovery (Guardians of Sunfist)
    ;918wands exclude add <phrase> | remove <phrase> | list | clear
    ;918wands info             - show this help

  Author: Claude Code, RuseOfFools
  Tags: wizard, duplicate, 918, wand, treasure, sell, utility
=end

module Wands918
  extend self

  SPELL_NUM     = 918
  MAX_PASSES    = 200                   # safety cap on outer rescans per container
  STOW          = Lich::Gemstone::StowList

  # -- Cast / sell result patterns ---------------------------------------------
  READY_RE           = /Your spell is ready\.|already have a spell (?:readied|prepared)/i
  DUP_SUCCESS_RE     = /grab the copy|splits into two, and slowly separates/i
  DUP_NOTSUITED_RE   = /not well suited for duplicating|cannot be duplicated|isn't something you can duplicate/i
  DUP_CATASTROPHE_RE = /puff of smoke|is destroyed|disintegrat|consumed in|explodes/i
  DUP_HANDS_RE       = /must be holding the object to be duplicated in your right hand/i
  # Works with any wand buyer (Cendadric, a pawnbroker, a clerk, etc.).
  SELL_OK_RE         = /hands you ([\d,]+) (?:silver|coins)/i
  SELL_FAIL_RE       = /not interested|isn't buying|can't sell that|won't buy|no interest|no use for (?:that|it)|I have no use|not something I|I'm sorry.*but I (?:have no|can't)/i
  SELL_NOSHOP_RE     = /can't (?:sell|do) that here|no one here (?:to|who|is)|no place to sell|nowhere to sell|not in a (?:shop|store)|isn't anyone here|no merchant|Sell to whom/i
  LOOK_END_RE        = /<container|In the|You see|That is closed|There (?:is|are) nothing|can't look inside|not something you can look/i

  # Non-destructive venue probe: APPRAISE offers a price without selling, so we
  # can confirm a buyer is present in ANY shop before duplicating anything.
  APPRAISE_OK_RE     = /You ask .* to appraise|(?:give|offer) you [\d,]+ (?:silver|coin)|coins? for it|turns? .* over in (?:his|her|their|its) hands|worth about|I'll give you/i
  APPRAISE_NO_RE     = /no one here|no merchant|isn't anyone here|can't do that here|Appraise what\?|no place to|not in a (?:shop|store)|There is no one|nobody here|Appraise to whom/i

  # Success line when pulling an item from any container type. Mirrors eloot's
  # retrieval regex (concealed pockets/cloaks say "You retrieve...", others use
  # slip/draw/grab/etc.) so we match immediately instead of waiting on timeout.
  GET_OK_RE   = /^You (?:shield the opening of .*? from view as you |discreetly |carefully |deftly |slowly )?(?:get|pick up|remove|draw|equip|grab|reach|slip|tuck|retrieve|already have|unsheathe|detach|swap|sling|withdraw)\b/i
  GET_FAIL_RE = /What were you referring to|I don't (?:see|know)|isn't here|can't quite|You can't|There is nothing/i

  # Society mana-recovery abilities, keyed by Society.member.
  # [spell, cooldown-or-punishment checker] mirrors ewaggle's usage.
  SOCIETY_MANA = {
    "Council of Light"     => { setting: "use_wracking", label: "Sign of Wracking",  spell: 9918 },
    "Guardians of Sunfist" => { setting: "use_power",    label: "Sigil of Power",    spell: 9718 },
    "Order of Voln"        => { setting: "use_mana",     label: "Symbol of Mana",    spell: 9813 },
  }.freeze

  def run
    load_settings
    tokens = Array(Array(Script.current.vars)[1..-1]).map(&:to_s)
    sub    = tokens[0].to_s.strip.downcase

    case sub
    when "info", "help", "?"
      usage
      return
    when "wracking", "mana", "power"
      config_society(sub, tokens[1])
      return
    when "exclude", "exclusion", "exclusions", "keep"
      config_exclude(tokens[1..-1])
      return
    end

    unless Spell[SPELL_NUM].known?
      echo "You do not know Duplicate (#{SPELL_NUM}). Aborting."
      return
    end

    containers, label = containers_for(sub)
    if containers.nil? || containers.empty?
      return # containers_for already explained why
    end

    @sold_count   = 0
    @silver_total = 0
    @failures     = []   # [{name:, reason:}]
    @abort        = false

    # Confirm a buyer is here (works in any pawnshop / wand-buying shop) using a
    # non-destructive appraise before we duplicate anything.
    unless venue_sells_wands?(containers)
      echo "No wand buyer is here. Stand in a pawnshop (or a shop that buys wands) first. Aborting."
      return
    end

    echo "918wands: #{label}"
    echo "Buyer confirmed. Wands that fail to duplicate are left in place, unsold."
    if (regen = active_regen_label)
      echo "Mana recovery: #{regen} enabled."
    end
    echo "Excluding (never sold): #{@sell_exclude.join('; ')}" unless @sell_exclude.empty?

    containers.each do |c|
      break if @abort
      process_container(c)
    end

    echo "Stopped: no buyer available to complete a sale." if @abort
    report
  end

  # -- Resolve which containers to work through --------------------------------
  # Returns [array_of_container_GameObjs, human_label]
  def containers_for(arg)
    case arg
    when "all"
      cons = GameObj.inv.to_a   # every worn item; non-containers yield no wands
      [cons, "scanning ALL worn containers for wands"]
    when "", nil
      STOW.check(silent: true, quiet: true) unless STOW.checked?
      wand_con = STOW.wand
      if wand_con.nil?
        echo "No WAND stow container is set. In game: STOW WAND <container>."
        echo "Or run:  ;918wands <container-noun>   or   ;918wands all"
        return [nil, nil]
      end
      [[wand_con], "using your wand container (#{wand_con.name})"]
    else
      con = resolve_container(arg)
      if con.nil?
        echo "Could not find a worn container with noun '#{arg}'."
        echo "Try:  ;918wands <container-noun>   |   ;918wands all   |   ;918wands info"
        return [nil, nil]
      end
      [[con], "using container '#{con.name}'"]
    end
  end

  # -- Work through one container until it holds no duplicatable wands ----------
  def process_container(container)
    skip_ids = []   # wands that stay put (failed/kept) - don't retry forever
    passes = 0
    loop do
      passes += 1
      break if passes > MAX_PASSES

      wands = wands_in(container).reject { |w| skip_ids.include?(w.id) }
      break if wands.empty?

      wands.each do |wand|
        break if @abort
        outcome = process_wand(wand, container)
        # :sold and :destroyed consume the wand; anything else leaves it in the
        # container, so remember it to avoid an infinite rescan.
        skip_ids << wand.id unless outcome == :sold || outcome == :destroyed
      end
      break if @abort
    end
  end

  # -- Per-wand workflow -------------------------------------------------------
  # Returns one of :sold, :not_suited, :destroyed, :error
  def process_wand(wand, container)
    wand_name = wand.name
    wand_id   = wand.id

    empty_right_hand if GameObj.right_hand.id
    empty_left_hand  if GameObj.left_hand.id
    waitrt?

    unless get_into_right_hand(wand_id)
      note_failure(wand_name, "could not retrieve from container")
      return :error
    end
    held = GameObj.right_hand

    ensure_prepared
    result = dothistimeout("cast my #{held.noun}", 8,
                           Regexp.union(DUP_SUCCESS_RE, DUP_NOTSUITED_RE,
                                        DUP_CATASTROPHE_RE, DUP_HANDS_RE,
                                        /You don't have a spell prepared|lose your concentration/i))
    waitcastrt?
    waitrt?

    case result
    when DUP_SUCCESS_RE
      sell_held_wands(container)
      :sold
    when DUP_NOTSUITED_RE
      note_failure(wand_name, "not a fresh treasure wand (not duplicatable)")
      return_to_container(held, container)
      :not_suited
    when DUP_CATASTROPHE_RE
      note_failure(wand_name, "CATASTROPHIC failure - wand destroyed")
      :destroyed
    when DUP_HANDS_RE
      note_failure(wand_name, "hand check failed (left hand not empty?)")
      return_to_container(held, container)
      :error
    else
      note_failure(wand_name, "no/unknown response to cast (#{result.inspect})")
      return_to_container(held, container)
      :error
    end
  end

  # After a successful duplicate we hold the original (right) and copy (left).
  # Sell every wand currently in hand (re-reading hands each time).
  def sell_held_wands(container)
    2.times do
      wand = [GameObj.right_hand, GameObj.left_hand].find { |h| h && h.id && h.noun == "wand" }
      break unless wand
      case try_sell(wand)
      when :sold
        # done
      when :noshop
        @abort = true
        note_failure(wand.name, "no buyer available to complete the sale")
        return_to_container(wand, container)
        break
      else # :refused
        note_failure(wand.name, "buyer would not purchase")
        return_to_container(wand, container)
      end
      waitrt?
    end
  end

  # Sell a specific held wand. Prefer the precise #id reference, fall back to
  # the noun form ("sell wand"). Returns :sold, :refused, or :noshop.
  def try_sell(wand)
    res = dothistimeout("sell ##{wand.id}", 6,
                        Regexp.union(SELL_OK_RE, SELL_NOSHOP_RE, SELL_FAIL_RE,
                                     /Sell what|don't (?:know|see)|isn't here/i))
    # If the #id form wasn't understood, retry with the plain noun form.
    if res.nil? || res =~ /Sell what|don't (?:know|see)|isn't here/i
      res = dothistimeout("sell #{wand.noun}", 6,
                          Regexp.union(SELL_OK_RE, SELL_NOSHOP_RE, SELL_FAIL_RE))
    end

    if res =~ SELL_OK_RE
      @sold_count += 1; @silver_total += $1.delete(',').to_i
      :sold
    elsif res =~ SELL_NOSHOP_RE
      :noshop
    else
      :refused
    end
  end

  # Non-destructive check that a buyer is present. Pulls the first wand it can
  # find, APPRAISES it (offers a price, no sale), returns it, and reads the
  # result. Ambiguous/unknown responses default to true so the sell-time
  # no-shop guard remains the final backstop.
  def venue_sells_wands?(containers)
    containers.each do |c|
      sample = wands_in(c).first
      next unless sample

      empty_right_hand if GameObj.right_hand.id
      empty_left_hand  if GameObj.left_hand.id
      next unless get_into_right_hand(sample.id)

      res = dothistimeout("appraise ##{GameObj.right_hand.id}", 6,
                          Regexp.union(APPRAISE_OK_RE, APPRAISE_NO_RE))
      waitrt?
      return_to_container(GameObj.right_hand, c)
      return false if res =~ APPRAISE_NO_RE
      return true
    end
    true # no wands anywhere to probe; nothing to sell regardless
  end

  # -- Settings ----------------------------------------------------------------
  def load_settings
    @use_wracking = CharSettings["use_wracking"] || false   # Council of Light
    @use_power    = CharSettings["use_power"]    || false   # Guardians of Sunfist
    @use_mana     = CharSettings["use_mana"]     || false   # Order of Voln
    @sell_exclude = Array(CharSettings["sell_exclude"])     # names never sold
    @sell_exclude_regex = build_word_boundary_regexes(@sell_exclude)
  end

  # Word-boundary union of the exclusion list (mirrors eloot). Empty list yields
  # /(?!)/ which matches nothing, so an empty list excludes nothing.
  def build_word_boundary_regexes(list)
    Regexp.union(
      Array(list).map do |r|
        source = r.is_a?(Regexp) ? r.source : r.to_s
        /\b(?:#{source})\b/i
      end
    )
  end

  def excluded?(obj)
    obj.name.to_s.match?(@sell_exclude_regex)
  end

  # -- Society mana recovery ---------------------------------------------------
  # Label of the enabled recovery ability that matches the current society, or nil.
  def active_regen_label
    cfg = SOCIETY_MANA[Society.member]
    return nil unless cfg
    return nil unless regen_enabled?(cfg[:setting])
    cfg[:label]
  rescue StandardError
    nil
  end

  def regen_enabled?(setting)
    { "use_wracking" => @use_wracking, "use_power" => @use_power, "use_mana" => @use_mana }[setting]
  end

  # Cast the society-appropriate mana ability once, if enabled and usable.
  # Returns true if it cast something (caller then rechecks mana).
  def recover_mana_via_society
    cfg = SOCIETY_MANA[Society.member]
    return false unless cfg && regen_enabled?(cfg[:setting])

    case Society.member
    when "Council of Light"
      wrack = Spell[9918]; punishment = Spell[9012]
      return false unless wrack.affordable? && !punishment.active?
      return false if Char.percent_health < 40                 # don't wrack while hurt
      return false if Room.current.tags.include?("no-magic")
      waitrt?; waitcastrt?
      wrack.cast
      true
    when "Guardians of Sunfist"
      sigil = Spell[9718]
      return false unless sigil.affordable?
      waitrt?; waitcastrt?
      sigil.cast
      true
    when "Order of Voln"
      return false if Effects::Cooldowns.active?("Symbol of Mana")
      waitrt?; waitcastrt?
      res = Spell[9813].cast
      if res.to_s =~ /^You strain to perform the symbol/
        echo "Out of favor - disabling Symbol of Mana for this run."
        @use_mana = false
        return false
      end
      true
    else
      false
    end
  rescue StandardError
    false
  end

  # -- Config subcommands ------------------------------------------------------
  def config_society(which, value)
    key   = { "wracking" => "use_wracking", "mana" => "use_mana", "power" => "use_power" }[which]
    label = { "wracking" => "Sign of Wracking (Council of Light)",
              "mana"     => "Symbol of Mana (Order of Voln)",
              "power"    => "Sigil of Power (Guardians of Sunfist)" }[which]

    if value.nil? || value.strip.empty?
      echo "#{label} mana recovery is currently #{CharSettings[key] ? 'ON' : 'OFF'}."
      return
    end

    on = value.strip.downcase =~ /\A(on|true|yes|1|enable)\z/
    CharSettings[key] = !!on
    echo "#{label} mana recovery #{on ? 'ENABLED' : 'DISABLED'}."
    echo "(Your current society is #{safe_society}.)"
  end

  def config_exclude(rest)
    rest   = Array(rest)
    action = rest[0].to_s.strip.downcase
    text   = rest[1..-1].to_a.join(" ").strip
    list   = Array(CharSettings["sell_exclude"])

    case action
    when "add"
      if text.empty?
        echo "Usage: ;918wands exclude add <wand name or phrase>"
      elsif list.any? { |e| e.casecmp?(text) }
        echo "Already excluded: #{text}"
      else
        list << text
        CharSettings["sell_exclude"] = list
        echo "Excluded (never sold): #{text}"
      end
    when "remove", "del", "delete", "rem"
      before = list.size
      list.reject! { |e| e.casecmp?(text) }
      CharSettings["sell_exclude"] = list
      echo list.size < before ? "Removed exclusion: #{text}" : "Not found in exclusions: #{text}"
    when "clear"
      CharSettings["sell_exclude"] = []
      echo "Cleared all sell exclusions."
    else # list / empty / anything else
      if list.empty?
        echo "No sell exclusions set. Add one with:  ;918wands exclude add <phrase>"
      else
        echo "Sell exclusions (matched wands are never duplicated or sold):"
        list.each { |e| echo "   - #{e}" }
      end
    end
  end

  def safe_society
    Society.member.to_s.empty? ? "none" : Society.member
  rescue StandardError
    "unknown"
  end

  # -- Helpers -----------------------------------------------------------------
  def resolve_container(noun)
    GameObj.inv.to_a.find { |o| o.noun == noun } ||
      GameObj.inv.to_a.find { |o| o.name =~ /\b#{Regexp.escape(noun)}\b/i }
  end

  def wands_in(container)
    # Silently refresh contents (also no-ops harmlessly on non-containers in
    # "all" mode). Open it first if it's closed.
    res = Lich::Util.issue_command("look in ##{container.id}", LOOK_END_RE,
                                   /<prompt/, silent: true, quiet: true, timeout: 5)
    if res.any? { |l| l =~ /That is closed/i }
      Lich::Util.issue_command("open ##{container.id}", /You open|already open/i,
                               /<prompt/, silent: true, quiet: true, timeout: 5)
      Lich::Util.issue_command("look in ##{container.id}", LOOK_END_RE,
                               /<prompt/, silent: true, quiet: true, timeout: 5)
    end
    Array(GameObj.containers[container.id]).select { |o| o.noun == "wand" && !excluded?(o) }
  rescue StandardError
    []
  end

  def get_into_right_hand(wand_id)
    dothistimeout("get ##{wand_id}", 5, Regexp.union(GET_OK_RE, GET_FAIL_RE))
    waitrt?
    GameObj.right_hand && GameObj.right_hand.id.to_s == wand_id.to_s
  end

  def ensure_prepared
    fput("release") if checkprep != "None" && checkprep !~ /Duplicate/i
    return if checkprep =~ /Duplicate/i

    last_notice = nil
    until Spell[SPELL_NUM].affordable?
      next if recover_mana_via_society   # cast society ability, then recheck
      if last_notice.nil? || (Time.now - last_notice) >= 60
        echo "Waiting for mana to prepare Duplicate (need #{Spell[SPELL_NUM].mana_cost}, have #{checkmana})..."
        last_notice = Time.now
      end
      sleep 2
    end
    dothistimeout("prepare #{SPELL_NUM}", 5, READY_RE)
    waitcastrt?
  end

  def return_to_container(obj, container)
    return if obj.nil? || obj.id.nil?
    dothistimeout("put ##{obj.id} in ##{container.id}", 5, /You put|already|You can't/i)
    waitrt?
  end

  def note_failure(name, reason)
    @failures << { name: name, reason: reason }
    echo ">> NOTE: #{name} -- #{reason}"
  end

  def report
    echo "============================================================"
    echo " 918wands - summary"
    echo "------------------------------------------------------------"
    echo " Wands sold (incl. copies): #{@sold_count}"
    echo " Silver earned:             #{@silver_total.to_s.reverse.gsub(/(\d{3})(?=\d)/, '\1,').reverse}"
    if @failures.empty?
      echo " Failures:                  none"
    else
      echo " Failures (#{@failures.size}) - these were NOT sold:"
      @failures.each { |f| echo "   - #{f[:name]}: #{f[:reason]}" }
    end
    echo "============================================================"
  end

  def usage
    echo "918wands - liquidate treasure wands with Duplicate (918)"
    echo ""
    echo "Run:"
    echo "  ;918wands              process wands in your WAND stow container"
    echo "  ;918wands all          process wands in EVERY worn container"
    echo "  ;918wands <container>   process wands in <container> noun"
    echo "  ;918wands info          show this help"
    echo ""
    echo "Mana recovery while waiting (enable the one for YOUR society):"
    echo "  ;918wands wracking on|off   Sign of Wracking  (Council of Light)"
    echo "  ;918wands mana on|off       Symbol of Mana    (Order of Voln)"
    echo "  ;918wands power on|off      Sigil of Power    (Guardians of Sunfist)"
    echo "  (only the ability matching your current society is used)"
    echo ""
    echo "Never-sell exclusions (matched wands are skipped entirely):"
    echo "  ;918wands exclude add <phrase>      e.g. exclude add lustrous beryl"
    echo "  ;918wands exclude remove <phrase>"
    echo "  ;918wands exclude list"
    echo "  ;918wands exclude clear"
    echo ""
    echo "Stand in any shop that buys wands (a pawnshop, Cendadric's, etc.)."
    echo "The default container is read from your in-game STOW WAND setting."
    echo "Only wands that successfully duplicate are sold; any that fail are"
    echo "left where they are, unsold, and reported at the end."
  end
end

before_dying do
  fput("release") if defined?(checkprep) && checkprep =~ /Duplicate/i
end

Wands918.run
